  <heading>AESMC</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>AES mix columns</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction reads a 16-byte state array
from each 128-bit segment of the source register, and
performs a single round of the MixColumns()
transformation on each state array in accordance with
the AES standard. Each updated state array is destructively placed in
the corresponding segment of the first source vector. This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
      <para>ID_AA64ZFR0_EL1.AES indicates whether this instruction is implemented.</para>
      <para>This instruction is legal when executed in Streaming SVE mode if one of the following is true:</para>
      <list type="unordered">
        <listitem>
          <content>Both FEAT_SSVE_AES and FEAT_SVE_AES are implemented.</content>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <content>FEAT_SME_FA64 is implemented and enabled.</content>
        </listitem>
      </list>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
    <sm_policy>SM_0_or_SSVE_AES</sm_policy>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
